            <title>[KAFKA-3216] &quot;Modifying topics&quot; section incorrectly says you can&apos;t change replication factor.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3216</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;Modifying Topics&quot; section of the docs (&lt;a href=&quot;http://kafka.apache.org/documentation.html#basic_ops_modify_topic&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://kafka.apache.org/documentation.html#basic_ops_modify_topic&lt;/a&gt;) says &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt; Kafka does not currently support reducing the number of partitions for a topic or changing the replication factor. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But you &lt;b&gt;can&lt;/b&gt; modify the replication factor. That second half of the sentence should be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
